Description:
Our harem style baby shorts were developed when Jordan, owner & mom of boy/girl twins, got tired of retiring mass amounts of expensive baby pants after just a couple weeks of wear!  Our unique harem style fit features soft & stretchy cotton waist and cuff bands, a longer crotch and versatile legs that can be scrunched up or stretched out as baby grows.  Our harem style shorts grow with your baby!
We hand select our classic & timeless print collections to coordinate with just about any style, so parents end up loving our harem leggings just as much as their little ones do!  Sorry, their not available in adult sizes yet!! ;)
Since our harem style baby shorts are designed with the versatility to fit a much wider age range, our sizes run from 0-6 months, 6-12 months, 12-24 months, 2T-3T, and in most cases will fit baby far beyond each age span ... which means baby has more time to wear, and you have more time to love!  These shorts are crafted from a soft, stretchy cotton / spandex / polyester blend.

Description:
Original Thai/Cambodian temple rubbing on rice paper from Angkor Wat, first a Hindu, then subsequently a Buddhist, temple complex in Cambodia and the largest religious monument in the world. This piece was created prior to 1967; the art of temple rubbing has been banned by the Cambodian government in an attempt to preserve the beauty of the Temples. 
Measures 21"x 29.75`" 
Condition appears overall very good: artwork is adhered between matte boards, small areas of paper lifting off from back matte, small area of foxing along upper left corner, water stains in lower portions, mostly in matte margins, matte has some age related yellowing, minor edge wear on back matte- does not affect the image and can easily be concealed with a frame.

Product name: The Vixen Perfume Oil - Organic Perfume - Vegan Perfume
Description:
Flirty, elusive, captivating, and mischievous. Those are the words that come to mind when I breathe in this perfume. It makes me want to lean closer, inhale deeper, and try to decipher how such a simple blend of fragrances leaves me so intrigued. 
An alluring mélange of floral and earthy notes make up this perfume, with organic jojoba oil serving as the carrier, organic vetiver essential oil acting as the base, organic ylang ylang essential oil the heart, and organic lavender essential oil the head. 
Perfect for free spirits, first dates, anniversaries, a quick mood boost, or as a gift for a loved one or a close friend. 
Packaged in a recyclable glass roll-top bottle with a compostable label, and shipped in recycled, recyclable packaging so you can feel good about what's inside AND outside your perfume. 
Looking for a different scent profile? Check out our other two organic perfumes:
The Dreamer:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/385312402/the-dreamer-organic-perfume-oil-organic
The Goddess:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/461530430/the-goddess-organic-perfume
**A FEW NOTES**
- Those pregnant or breastfeeding should not use this blend, as the side effects of many essential oils are not fully known due to lack of clinical testing. 
- This is an all-natural product made with sterilized equipment and no natural or chemical preservatives. For best results, store in a cool, dark place and use within six months of purchase. Make sure to leave the perfume tightly capped between uses, as adding dirt or water to any preservative-free product could introduce some yucky bacteria into the mix. 
PRO TIP: if a natural product looks or smells off, discontinue use. 
*For external use only. Keep out of reach of children. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. This information has not been evaluated by the FDA. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease.

Product name: Contact Microphone - high quality, durable construction.  3 foot cable with 1/4" plug
Description:
A durable, versatile contact microphone constructed of professional grade components.  This hand made mic was designed to perform to high standards while enduring the rigors of road use and a wide range of applications.  It is made with a 27mm brass piezo disc, Audio Technica mic cable, and a professional gold-plated 1/4" mono plug.  The piezo disc is double dipped in rubberized paint to improve solder joint strength and provide water resistance.  Finally, a short length of heat shrink tubing is shrunk around the cable to prevent any peeling of the rubber paint.
These contact mics can be taped or clamped to any surface to create audio from any source of vibrations.  Affix one to a bottle and use for percussion, tape one to the body of your guitar to pick up unique tones.  Use them in any live setting and they're highly resistant to feedback.  My contact mics also work well as drum triggers.  The possibilities are endless!
Contact mics can be made to order, i.e. with 1/8" plug, a female jack, or with different cable lengths.  Message me with any requests or questions.

Product name: Monogrammed wedding napkins Personalized wedding reception napkins monogram set of 50
Description:
These napkins feature a single, elegant Edwardian monogram letter and use Bernhard Tango style font for your names and date. 
Napkin color in photo: Burgundy
After you have made your purchase, please provide all your order information in the "notes to seller" during checkout:
1) Date you need your order
2) Napkin color
3) Print color
4) Text you want printed
5) Single monogram letter 
 To guide you through this process, please read all the following information, then feel free to contact me with any questions. I am always happy to help and will get back to you quickly.
Pricing:
My napkins are sold in quantities of 50, if you choose 1, you will be purchasing 50 napkins, 2 will be 100, 3 will be 150... etc.
Beverage size napkins - 17 per 50 napkins
Luncheon size napkins - 20 per 50 napkins
1) Date you need your order – I usually ship within 5 - 7 days of payment, but want to be sure your order is to you in time for your event.
2) Napkin color – I use high quality 3-ply napkins. Beverage size is 5” x 5”. Luncheon size is 6 1/2" x 6 1/2". Both sizes are available in 27 colors. Matching napkin colors to event colors can be a challenge. If you require an exact color match, please contact me and I will be happy to send you free napkin samples in the mail. You may choose different napkin colors in quantities of 50. Please note: the napkins in the photos have been printed on beverage napkins. If you are ordering luncheon napkins, there will be more open space around the printed image.
3) Print color- Choose a print color that has as much contrast to your napkin color so it really “pops”. Print colors are available in Matte and Metallic. Let me know if you need help choosing a print color. 
 
4) Text to be printed – Choose your own wording! You can choose up to 3 lines of type, 24 maximum characters per line including spaces.  Please be sure and double check spelling and punctuation. If you prefer a different style of font than in the photos for your napkins, let me know in the notes to seller when you check out and I will send you my font choice file.
5) Single monogram letter. Please see 2nd photo in this listing which shows the style of all my monogram letters.
Other Information:
For orders of 150 napkins, I can send an electronic proof. Let me know when you check out if you require a proof.
Shipping – Most orders ship within 5 – 7 days of payment. If there is a delay in your order, I will contact you immediately.
Quantity to Order? - If you are just wanting napkins for cake, 1 napkin per person is enough. If you need them for cake, appetizers and bar, 3 - 4 napkins per person should be enough.
International Customers - I do ship international, please contact me for a shipping quote. Let me know where you are located and the amount and size of napkins you are interested in ordering.
All machinery and supplies made in the US.
Thank you for visiting my Etsy shop, I look forward to working with you! Tere Quade / TQ Unique Napkins

Care Instructions:
Although our jewelry are high quality with extra layers of coat for long lasting, yet plated jewelry should be cleaned periodically. To extend the life of your jewelry, it’s very important that you keep it dry (never bathe or spray perfume on your jewelry, chemical reactions with chlorine and other elements such as perspiration can lead to tarnishing). Remove jewelry when sleeping, exercising, or doing physical activities, as prolonged contact with sweat will cause the plating to wear away faster. Never use abrasives chemicals or products to clean your jewelry. After each wear, gently wipe each piece of jewelry clean of make up and skin oils with a soft, lint-free cloth in order to avoid scratching. Since rose gold pieces are more sensitive because of copper usage (in order to turn the color from gold to rose gold), please care as instructed above.
